HEADWORD: Rigadoon
<hw>Rig`a*doon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>rigadon</ets>, <ets>rigaudon</ets>.]</ety> <def>A gay, lively dance
for one couple, -- said to have been borrowed from Provence in
France.</def> <rj><au>W. Irving.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose dancing dogs in <qex>rigadoons</qex> excel.</q>
<rj><qau>Wolcott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riga fir</ent>⟦br⟧
